                                </div>
                                <p>Be aware that many common symbols and dingbat Unicode characters will appear as <code>multicolored</code> pictographs due to the <code>font</code> stack's inclusion of emoji fonts. They won't be impacted by any CSS <code>color</code> schemes, and their look will vary based on the native emoji font of the browser or platform.</p>
                                
                                <p>The <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> is given this font <code>family</code>, and UX4G as a whole automatically inherits it. Recompile UX4G and edit <code>$font-family-base</code> to change the system font family.</p>

                                <h2>Headings and paragraphs <a href="" id="Headings-and-paragraphs"
                                        class="opacity-0 hover-1">#</a> </h2>
                                <p>All heading elements—e.g., <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>—and <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> are
                                    reset to have their <code>margin-top</code> removed. Headings have
                                    <code>margin-bottom: .5rem</code> added and
                                    paragraphs <code>margin-bottom: 1rem</code> for
                                    easy spacing.
                                </p>
