                                <h2 class="mt-20">HTML5 <code>[hidden]</code> attribute <a href=""
                                        id="HTML5-<code>[hidden]</code>-attribute"></a> </h2>
                                <p>The <code>[hidden]</code> global attribute in HTML5 has the default styling of display: none. We improve on this default, taking a cue from PureCSS, by setting <code>[hidden]</code> <code> {display: none!important;}</code> to help stop its display from being unintentionally overridden.</p>
                                <p>The jQuery $(...)<code>.hide</code>() and $(...)<code>.show()</code> methods do not work with <code>[hidden]</code>. Because of this, it is not strongly recommend <code>[hidden]</code> above other methods of controlling the visibility of items.</p>
                                <p>Use the.invisible class in its place to just toggle an element's visibility, leaving the element's presentation unaltered and allowing it to continue influencing the document's flow.</p>

                                

